%I A396053 #8 May 19 2026 00:16:50
%S A396053 0,0,0,39,8631,1269960
%N A396053 Number of relations R on an n-element set such that the transitive closure of R has exactly four elements more than R.
%C A396053 Equivalently, a(n) is the number of binary relations R on an n-set for which exactly four ordered pairs must be adjoined to obtain a transitive relation; i.e., |closure(R) \ R| = 4.
%e A396053 For n = 0, 1 every relation is transitive, so a(0) = a(1) = 0.
%e A396053 For n = 3, one of the a(3) = 39 relations is R = {(1, 1), (1, 2), (1, 3), (2, 1), (3, 1)}, whose transitive closure R = [3] X [3] adds exactly the four pairs (2, 2), (2, 3), (3, 2), (3, 3).
%Y A396053 Cf. A006905, A395083, A395919, A395920.
%K A396053 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A396053 0,4
